| Canadian Politicians Demand DMCA                                   |
|   from the couldn't-blame-canada-then dept.                        |
|   posted by kdawson on Thursday June 21, @13:01 (Music)            |
|   http://politics.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/06/21/164258      |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

An anonymous reader writes "Michael Geist is reporting that a Canadian
parliamentary committee has [0]demanded that the government establish a
Canadian DMCA. The demand, which comes in a [1]study on counterfeiting
and piracy (PDF) released on Wednesday night, recommends ratification of
the WIPO Internet treaties, increasing damage awards for copyright
infringement, creating new offenses for selling modification devices, and
encouraging prosecutors to seek jail time for piracy violations."

