| Subcommittee Stops Human Mars Mission Spending                     |
|   from the who-wants-to-go-there-anyway dept.                      |
|   posted by Zonk on Thursday June 21, @16:00 (Space)               |
|   http://science.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/06/21/1926222      |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

An anonymous reader writes "Last week's House Appropriations Subcommittee
for Commerce, Justice, and Science FY08 budget markup would prevent work
on programs devoted to human missions to Mars. According to a House
Appropriations Committee [0]press release, the markup language states
that NASA cannot pursue "development or demonstration activity related
exclusively to Human Exploration of Mars. NASA has too much on its plate
already, and the President is welcome to include adequate funding for the
Human Mars Initiative in a budget amendment or subsequent year funding
requests." The Mars Society is already leading an [1]effort to get the
language removed."

Discuss this story at:
    http://science.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/06/21/1926222

Links:
    0. http://appropriations.house.gov/pdf/Mollohan%20SubC%202008.pdf
    1. http://www.marssociety.org/portal/Members/jlagarde/saveMarsBudget2007/


